        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>You can create remedies and other herbal products. You gain the basic alchemy benefits (page 150), though they apply only for herbal items: alchemical items with the healing trait, plus <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.equipment-srd\" data-id=\"ktjFOp3U0wQD9t0Z\" draggable=\"true\"> Antidote</a> and <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.equipment-srd\" data-id=\"UqinuuCWePTYGhVO\" draggable=\"true\"> Antiplague</a>.</p>\n<p>You gain batches of infused reagents per day equal to your level or half your level if you didn't make your daily preparations in the wilderness. Your <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.classfeatures\" data-id=\"Pe0zmIqyTBc2Td0I\" draggable=\"true\"> Advanced Alchemy</a> level for creating these is 1 and doesn't increase on its own.</p>\n<p>You become an expert in Nature and can use Nature instead of Crafting to <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.actionspf2e\" data-id=\"rmwa3OyhTZ2i2AHl\" draggable=\"true\"> Craft</a> herbal items. You don't need to be trained in Crafting or have the <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.feats-srd\" data-id=\"is3Oz9wt11lNq62K\" draggable=\"true\"> Alchemical Crafting</a> feat to do so, and you can use <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.equipment-srd\" data-id=\"s1vB3HdXjMigYAnY\" draggable=\"true\"> Healer's Tools</a> instead of <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.equipment-srd\" data-id=\"4ftXXUCBHcf4b0MH\" draggable=\"true\"> Alchemist's Tools</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Special</strong> You can't select another dedication feat until you have gained two other feats from the herbalist archetype.</p>"
